4
00:00:39,726 --> 00:00:42,466
You were the final decision maker on the tower crane purchase.

5
00:00:42,466 --> 00:00:45,066
You used that power to purchase a tower crane...

6
00:00:45,066 --> 00:00:46,807
without knowing when it was made at a normal price.

7
00:00:46,807 --> 00:00:47,976
You took the difference in price...

8
00:00:48,136 --> 00:00:50,106
through Myung Tower.

9
00:00:50,476 --> 00:00:53,617
That feeble tower crane eventually fell and hurt people.

10
00:00:53,877 --> 00:00:55,277
To cover up for your corruption,

11
00:00:56,417 --> 00:00:57,787
you said the cause of the fall...

12
00:00:58,546 --> 00:00:59,586
was the wind?

13
00:01:00,217 --> 00:01:01,257
Gosh.

14
00:01:03,187 --> 00:01:05,226
You're a funny person.

15
00:01:06,187 --> 00:01:07,556
Can you prove it?

16
00:01:07,581 --> 00:01:08,721
Give me the laptop.

17
00:01:09,156 --> 00:01:12,796
How dare you talk about something you can't even prove in front of me?

18
00:01:12,997 --> 00:01:15,367
I'm going to fire you from the board for defamation.

19
00:01:15,437 --> 00:01:17,666
You will be remembered as the Audit Team manager...

20
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:20,007
who I fired after the shortest amount of time.

21
00:01:20,007 --> 00:01:21,137
Someone is hiding...

22
00:01:21,476 --> 00:01:24,247
the injury of the tower crane operator.

23
00:01:25,276 --> 00:01:27,177
I think it's Mr. Bae.

24
00:01:27,516 --> 00:01:29,147
What do you think?

25
00:01:40,526 --> 00:01:41,826
Mr. Hwang is here.

26
00:01:42,257 --> 00:01:43,966
You're done for.

27
00:01:44,996 --> 00:01:46,097
Be careful.

28
00:01:54,976 --> 00:01:57,446
Look who's here.

29
00:01:59,347 --> 00:02:00,776
Gosh.

30
00:02:01,446 --> 00:02:03,476
- Have you been well? - Yes, sir.

31
00:02:04,617 --> 00:02:05,686
- This is Mr. Yang. - Hi.

32
00:02:10,787 --> 00:02:12,586
Mr. Shin. Aren't you going to greet him?

33
00:02:12,726 --> 00:02:14,597
What are you doing? Say hello to Mr. Hwang.

34
00:02:15,496 --> 00:02:16,496
Who is this?

35
00:02:16,496 --> 00:02:18,966
He's the new Audit Team manager.

36
00:02:23,166 --> 00:02:24,407
The Audit Team manager?

37
00:02:28,177 --> 00:02:29,336
Hurry up and say hello.

38
00:02:38,846 --> 00:02:40,286
Why is he looking at me like that?

39
00:02:40,887 --> 00:02:42,156
He's a lunatic.

40
00:02:52,526 --> 00:02:53,697
Come on.

41
00:03:06,276 --> 00:03:11,346
(The Auditors)

42
00:03:11,786 --> 00:03:13,656
(Episode 2)

43
00:03:13,656 --> 00:03:15,086
(Vice President Hwang Dae Woong)

44
00:03:15,216 --> 00:03:16,387
That was my doing.

45
00:03:17,586 --> 00:03:19,586
We should wrap up the construction as soon as possible.

46
00:03:19,586 --> 00:03:21,397
It costs an astronomical amount of money.

47
00:03:22,697 --> 00:03:24,167
Isn't wind a good reason?

48
00:03:27,566 --> 00:03:28,996
Covering up a small incident...

49
00:03:28,996 --> 00:03:30,466
caused a big accident.

50
00:03:30,566 --> 00:03:31,637
What accident?

51
00:03:31,637 --> 00:03:33,506
- I'm currently auditing. - Who?

52
00:03:33,506 --> 00:03:35,276
Mr. Seo Gil Pyo, Mr. Bae Young Sik,

53
00:03:35,276 --> 00:03:36,506
the president of Myung Tower,

54
00:03:37,306 --> 00:03:38,406
and...

55
00:03:42,617 --> 00:03:43,647
Me?

56
00:03:43,647 --> 00:03:45,846
I'll audit all individuals related to the tower crane corruption.

57
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,316
Both executives and staff alike.

58
00:03:50,086 --> 00:03:52,256
My goodness,

59
00:03:52,626 --> 00:03:53,857
I'm impressed.

60
00:03:54,697 --> 00:03:58,026
Where on earth did Se Woong find a gem like you?

61
00:03:58,066 --> 00:03:59,827
Foreman Bae Young Sik has fled.

62
00:04:00,297 --> 00:04:02,667
The laptop I need to audit also disappeared.

63
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:06,207
If you're done, I'll excuse myself.

64
00:04:06,906 --> 00:04:08,707
Hey, punk!

65
00:04:21,117 --> 00:04:23,017
That was what my old self would've said.

66
00:04:23,387 --> 00:04:24,656
But now, I don't swear because people report...

67
00:04:24,656 --> 00:04:25,786
to the Ministry of Employment and Labor nowadays.

68
00:04:27,496 --> 00:04:29,357
I'll tell you nicely, so listen up.

69
00:04:30,197 --> 00:04:31,427
If you don't find anything,

70
00:04:31,526 --> 00:04:33,297
you'll be held responsible for causing a ruckus.

71
00:04:36,797 --> 00:04:38,867
The Audit Team reports directly to the president.

72
00:04:39,566 --> 00:04:41,077
Please go through the president...

73
00:04:41,077 --> 00:04:43,477
to hold me responsible.

74
00:04:43,477 --> 00:04:44,607
It will be me.

75
00:04:48,177 --> 00:04:50,177
I'll make you pay for it.

76
00:05:16,006 --> 00:05:17,076
I'm back.

77
00:05:17,847 --> 00:05:18,977
What about Mr. Shin?

78
00:05:18,977 --> 00:05:20,376
He left already.

79
00:05:20,477 --> 00:05:21,547
Hey.

80
00:05:21,646 --> 00:05:23,646
- Foreman Bae disappeared. - What?

81
00:05:23,677 --> 00:05:25,746
He disappeared without paying the hospital bill.

82
00:05:26,087 --> 00:05:28,556
There really must be a scandal behind the tower crane.

83
00:05:29,487 --> 00:05:31,857
How did it go with Mr. Shin at Myung Tower?

84
00:05:32,756 --> 00:05:33,826
The laptop.

85
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,196
Hey.

86
00:05:38,826 --> 00:05:39,967
Get ready for a meeting.

87
00:05:48,876 --> 00:05:50,076
Mr. Bae Young Sik.

88
00:05:50,646 --> 00:05:52,847
Why did you conceal the reason that caused the crane to topple over?

89
00:05:52,907 --> 00:05:55,316
If the cause is a natural disaster,

90
00:05:55,316 --> 00:05:58,117
I hear we could be more speedy to resume the construction.

91
00:05:58,117 --> 00:05:59,946
This was decided by the higher-ups.

92
00:05:59,946 --> 00:06:01,857
I'd never decide on such a thing alone.

93
00:06:01,857 --> 00:06:02,956
Foreman Bae disappeared.

94
00:06:02,956 --> 00:06:04,626
He disappeared without paying the hospital bill.

95
00:06:04,626 --> 00:06:06,857
There really must be a scandal behind the tower crane.

96
00:06:06,857 --> 00:06:09,696
Someone is hiding the injury of the tower crane operator.

97
00:06:09,956 --> 00:06:11,927
I think it's Mr. Bae.

98
00:06:12,626 --> 00:06:14,337
What do you think?

99
00:06:15,936 --> 00:06:17,867
Those selected for the audit...

100
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:20,407
are either manipulating evidence or running off with evidence.

101
00:06:21,076 --> 00:06:22,337
If we don't hurry,

102
00:06:22,977 --> 00:06:24,646
all evidence will become useless.

103
00:06:25,646 --> 00:06:27,617
Fail to audit, and the company...

104
00:06:27,617 --> 00:06:29,376
will suffer direct damage.

105
00:06:29,677 --> 00:06:32,117
Focus, everyone.

106
00:06:36,157 --> 00:06:38,157
(President Hwang Se Woong)

107
00:06:45,826 --> 00:06:47,597
So you scouted the Audit Team Manager.

108
00:06:48,696 --> 00:06:50,936
There wasn't a need to import a hunting dog.

109
00:06:50,936 --> 00:06:52,306
We have countless of them here.

110
00:06:53,206 --> 00:06:54,737
Or are you trying to screw me up?

111
00:06:55,837 --> 00:06:57,306
You're going after Mr. Seo.

112
00:06:57,907 --> 00:07:00,146
Why is auditing Mr. Seo screwing you up?

113
00:07:00,146 --> 00:07:01,917
It's okay for him to skim company funds.

114
00:07:02,646 --> 00:07:04,146
Even Father turned a blind eye.

115
00:07:04,146 --> 00:07:05,516
That won't happen from now on.

116
00:07:05,516 --> 00:07:07,386
- On whose order? - My order.

117
00:07:08,617 --> 00:07:09,686
I'm the President.

118
00:07:11,326 --> 00:07:12,357
Right.

119
00:07:13,427 --> 00:07:16,097
Being the President is the best, isn't it?

120
00:07:23,297 --> 00:07:24,306
On the day of the accident,

121
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:28,607
But the tower crane operator...

122
00:07:28,607 --> 00:07:31,206
only suffered one broken leg.

123
00:07:31,206 --> 00:07:33,376
We're currently 12 stories high.

124
00:07:33,746 --> 00:07:35,617
He should've suffered serious injuries.

125
00:07:35,617 --> 00:07:38,816
Blood was found on the cabin chair headrest.

126
00:07:39,547 --> 00:07:42,787
In short, Mr. Bae ran away in fear he would get busted...

127
00:07:42,787 --> 00:07:44,787
for lying about the operator's extent of injury.

128
00:07:45,287 --> 00:07:48,326
He was worried he would get called toÂ account as the site foreman.

129
00:07:49,126 --> 00:07:50,797
Could this be the case?

130
00:07:50,797 --> 00:07:52,696
No. Listen.

131
00:07:52,996 --> 00:07:54,436
Had the operator suffered severe injuries,

132
00:07:54,436 --> 00:07:55,867
why didn't the hospital get in touch?

133
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:58,667
Or are you suggesting Mr. Bae and the hospital worked together?

134
00:07:58,837 --> 00:08:00,006
That's absurd.

135
00:08:00,006 --> 00:08:02,277
The operator was lucky and got away with just a broken leg.

136
00:08:02,277 --> 00:08:04,177
Did you question Mr. Choi Hyung Il?

137
00:08:05,376 --> 00:08:06,407
Did you do it?

138
00:08:07,316 --> 00:08:08,746
Without questioning him,

139
00:08:08,746 --> 00:08:10,717
how can you believe in such a miracle?

140
00:08:12,917 --> 00:08:15,617
Let's go question Mr. Choi right now.

141
00:08:16,217 --> 00:08:17,857
We should check...

142
00:08:17,857 --> 00:08:20,487
why Mr. Bae ran away and if he had a reason to.

143
00:08:22,357 --> 00:08:24,097
I'll look for Mr. Bae.

144
00:08:24,097 --> 00:08:27,196
There might be a way to find places he could've gone to.

145
00:08:27,196 --> 00:08:29,136
Why don't we split into teams?

146
00:08:29,566 --> 00:08:31,337
Ms. Ok and Mr. Moon will work together.

147
00:08:31,337 --> 00:08:32,936
Ms. Yoon and I will work together.

148
00:08:33,537 --> 00:08:36,576
It can't be helped. You are to work with Mr. Shin, Mr. Gu.

149
00:08:37,806 --> 00:08:39,876
Mr. Gu Han Soo will be transferred...

150
00:08:39,876 --> 00:08:40,977
to a different department.

151
00:08:42,117 --> 00:08:44,016
It's a decision I made as the manager.

152
00:08:44,946 --> 00:08:46,146
Wrap things up well.

153
00:08:49,756 --> 00:08:50,787
But...

154
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:02,867
Shin Cha Il asking for the laptop...

155
00:09:03,197 --> 00:09:05,636
means he doesn't have it.

156
00:09:05,636 --> 00:09:06,707
Right?

157
00:09:07,307 --> 00:09:09,707
Where on earth could the laptop be?

158
00:09:09,837 --> 00:09:11,376
It couldn't be collected.

159
00:09:11,746 --> 00:09:13,807
Maybe someone picked it up.

160
00:09:13,807 --> 00:09:15,617
That could be for the better.

161
00:09:17,217 --> 00:09:19,087
We shouldn't jump to conclusions.

162
00:09:20,046 --> 00:09:21,416
It must be found one way or another.

163
00:09:21,557 --> 00:09:24,557
In my opinion, you should report...

164
00:09:24,557 --> 00:09:27,926
to the Vice President yourself.

165
00:09:30,426 --> 00:09:31,467
Darn it.

166
00:09:33,526 --> 00:09:35,266
You can't drive a wrecked car.

167
00:09:35,597 --> 00:09:36,697
I called for a tow truck.

168
00:09:37,707 --> 00:09:38,737
Give me the car key.

169
00:09:40,406 --> 00:09:41,876
You're not well, are you?

170
00:09:42,136 --> 00:09:45,107
I already called our company car repair shop.

171
00:09:47,516 --> 00:09:49,347
This will take some time.

172
00:09:49,477 --> 00:09:51,187
We'll provide a company car for you.

173
00:09:51,617 --> 00:09:53,687
- Wait just a minute. - Thank you.

174
00:09:56,687 --> 00:09:58,557
Did you really not see the laptop?

175
00:10:00,526 --> 00:10:03,256
I remember nothing after getting dragged away by the thugs.

176
00:10:03,496 --> 00:10:05,727
When I woke up, you were already unconscious.

177
00:10:06,996 --> 00:10:10,496
There is information on the laptop that will conclude the audit.

178
00:10:11,406 --> 00:10:12,506
Do you have it?

179
00:10:13,006 --> 00:10:14,636
I really have no idea.

180
00:10:18,676 --> 00:10:20,847
- Goodness. - I'm in today, Mr. Choi.

181
00:10:20,847 --> 00:10:21,847
- I'm in. - It must be a delivery, Hyun Hee.

182
00:10:21,847 --> 00:10:22,847
Open the door.

183
00:10:22,847 --> 00:10:24,717
What's this? Darn it.

184
00:10:24,717 --> 00:10:27,217
- Good grief. - Seriously.

185
00:10:27,217 --> 00:10:29,286
- Let's do this. - Oh, no.

186
00:10:29,286 --> 00:10:30,827
Luck must be on your side.

187
00:10:30,827 --> 00:10:32,987
- Hi, kid. - Hi.

188
00:10:33,227 --> 00:10:35,396
- Who is he? - Hi. Who is Mr. Choi Hyung Il?

189
00:10:35,396 --> 00:10:36,626
That's me.

190
00:10:37,426 --> 00:10:38,996
We're from JU Construction.

191
00:10:38,996 --> 00:10:40,166
Please answer our questions.

192
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:45,207
Back then, the materials were being pulled up from the surface.

193
00:10:45,207 --> 00:10:48,207
But the tower crane collapsed with just the sudden gust of wind.

194
00:10:48,207 --> 00:10:50,077
I thought I was going to die.

195
00:10:50,077 --> 00:10:51,577
Struggling to live was futile.

196
00:10:51,577 --> 00:10:53,276
I passed out filled with regret.

197
00:10:53,807 --> 00:10:55,347
When I woke up, I was at the hospital.

198
00:10:56,347 --> 00:10:58,347
- You were really lucky. - I was.

199
00:10:59,217 --> 00:11:01,256
How do you know Mr. Bae Young Sik?

200
00:11:01,256 --> 00:11:05,156
He's the foreman of the site, and I'm the operator.

201
00:11:05,156 --> 00:11:07,026
So, no personal relationship?

202
00:11:07,026 --> 00:11:08,097
No, none.

203
00:11:08,526 --> 00:11:10,996
This is all I know. I can leave, right?

204
00:11:10,996 --> 00:11:12,666
- Yes. Thank you for your time. - No worries.

205
00:11:15,036 --> 00:11:17,967
Isn't everything clear now that the victim testified himself?

206
00:11:19,107 --> 00:11:21,906
He lied that the cause of the accident was the wind.

207
00:11:22,207 --> 00:11:24,947
He and Mr. Bae were junior and senior but didn't mention it.

208
00:11:24,947 --> 00:11:26,977
Why didn't you argue back?

209
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:30,276
I let him be. There's a limit to auditing a subcontractor's worker.

210
00:11:32,516 --> 00:11:33,516
Mr. Shin.

211
00:11:34,857 --> 00:11:36,957
Tell me what you're thinking.

212
00:11:37,626 --> 00:11:39,886
I really have no idea why you're stating...

213
00:11:40,957 --> 00:11:42,156
everyone is lying.

214
00:11:43,426 --> 00:11:46,266
What do you think Mr. Bae's inevitable circumstance is?

215
00:11:48,296 --> 00:11:50,737
Something might be going on with his family.

216
00:11:51,266 --> 00:11:53,166
With a sudden call, he could've been...

217
00:11:53,166 --> 00:11:54,437
That's unlikely.

218
00:11:54,776 --> 00:11:55,776
Go home.

219
00:12:02,947 --> 00:12:04,847
Mr. Bae's house, the sauna he frequents,

220
00:12:04,847 --> 00:12:07,217
the bar he's a regular at, and Mr. Kwak's house.

221
00:12:07,217 --> 00:12:09,857
I tried all the places he could be, but he wasn't there.

222
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:12,457
What about his daughter's place?

223
00:12:12,587 --> 00:12:14,197
She's the only family he has.

224
00:12:14,256 --> 00:12:16,057
That's going too far.

225
00:12:16,996 --> 00:12:18,567
Things could get complicated.

226
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:20,097
But without finding him,

227
00:12:20,197 --> 00:12:22,536
everything is a mystery.

228
00:12:23,266 --> 00:12:25,166
Let me visit. I've met her before.

229
00:12:25,337 --> 00:12:26,837
Send me the address.

230
00:12:28,176 --> 00:12:29,176
All right.

231
00:12:31,077 --> 00:12:32,077
Here, have some.

232
00:12:32,307 --> 00:12:33,506
Thank you.

233
00:12:34,477 --> 00:12:36,146
We met at my wedding, right?

234
00:12:36,347 --> 00:12:39,746
I remember my dad introducing you as his favorite.

235
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:40,916
I see.

236
00:12:47,526 --> 00:12:50,697
We're going to surprise my dad about it on his birthday.

237
00:12:50,697 --> 00:12:52,227
Please keep it from him.

238
00:12:52,626 --> 00:12:53,666
I will.

239
00:12:55,737 --> 00:12:58,136
By any chance...

240
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,937
Did you contact Mr. Bae today?

241
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:04,646
No, I didn't. Why do you ask?

242
00:13:05,676 --> 00:13:10,146
I should tell you as you're his family.

243
00:13:10,847 --> 00:13:13,286
Mr. Bae suffered a minor injury...

244
00:13:13,286 --> 00:13:15,317
and was admitted to the hospital.

245
00:13:15,317 --> 00:13:16,317
"Hospital?"

246
00:13:16,957 --> 00:13:18,987
It's nothing severe.

247
00:13:19,327 --> 00:13:21,857
But he suddenly left. I want to know why.

248
00:13:24,926 --> 00:13:27,597
- The call cannot be connected. - What? He's not picking up.

249
00:13:28,337 --> 00:13:30,067
Is something going on at the company?

250
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:49,016
There is information...

251
00:13:49,016 --> 00:13:51,286
on the laptop that will conclude the audit.

252
00:13:51,286 --> 00:13:52,286
Do you have it?

253
00:13:52,286 --> 00:13:53,487
With that,

254
00:13:53,487 --> 00:13:55,057
- you'll get transferred to Florida. - To Florida.

255
00:13:55,057 --> 00:13:56,857
- Foreman Bae will return. - Return.

256
